article.headline: Texas Southern 95, Texas-Arlington 81
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Jacques Jones scored 26 points and Sollie Norwood added 21 to lead Texas Southern to a 95-81 victory over Texas-Arlington on Wednesday night. Jones shot 11-of-16 from the field and 4-of-6 from the free throw line. Norwood came off the bench to hit 5-of-10 from the field, including 3-of-7 3-pointers. He also made all eight of his free throws. Dominique White and Chris Moore each scored 13 points for Texas Southern (3-6). Roger Guignard scored 19 points and Larry Posey had 14 for Texas-Arlington (3-6). Jermaine Griffin added 10. Texas Southern led 45-35 at the half. Texas Southern shot 52 percent from the field while Texas-Arlington shot 35 percent.
